The Labour Party is no longer the big community it used to be.
He is not tolerant of those who express their ideas
When activists from my local party's Momentum movement voted to censor me, it wasn't a surprise.
After all, I am the last of a line of Labour Party parliamentarians considered not welcome, all for expressing our ideas.
My parliamentary colleague Joan Ryan received the same treatment because she stood up against anti-Semitism.
