Some key facts about Palu and Donggala on Sulawesi Island:
Palu is the capital of the central province of Sulawesi, located at the tip of a narrow bay on the west coast of Sulawesi Island, whose population was estimated at 379,800 in 2017.
The city celebrated its 40th anniversary when the earthquakes and tsunamis took place.
Donggala is a regency that runs over 300 km (180 miles) of coastline northwest of Sulawesi Island.
